page.title: 01Humberside Countryside
page.content: This area is wet and flat 0'-150' above sea level some clay deposits are bases for ponds giving sanctury to Duck, Geese, Moorhen. Large fields of cereals, Rape vegetables with minimal hedgeing drain into man-made dykes. Highly mechanised farming with small labour force cattle and pigs reared inside buildings. Many footpaths across fields connect two small farming communities and outlying homesteads, all homes on mains water and electricity. Road-level bridges cross drains where they intersect with narrow metalled roads allowing passage to motorised vehicles. Mixed woodland gives cover to large variety of wild birds and animals including Pheasant, Heron, Squirrels. In the north - the west to east secondary road gives access to the coast but no access to arterial road running
